{
  "_comment": "Agent role manifest for FORGE. Keys = agent names (agent_type without the forge: prefix / .md). Values declare readonly:true (no writes) or allowedPaths (permitted Write/Edit target patterns); deniedPaths (when present) blocks matching paths even within allowedPaths. The PreToolUse hook ctx-pre-tool.js enforces this. allowedPaths corrected 2026-05-29 per the 28-role audit (run wf_179abfc0) to match each agent's REAL write-scope: docs/context/checkpoint.md for context-limit writers, the .pipeline/context/reviewer-output/ tree reviewers actually write to (not docs/context/), critic's findings (was wrongly readonly), coder's real source surface, documenter's real targets, skills-generator's skills/ subdir. Dead roles removed (tester, implementer, nyquist-auditor — no agent file). NOTE: the allow-list lookup stays DORMANT until ctx-pre-tool normalizes the forge: prefix (TODO a634c98c, warn-first rollout) — these corrections make it accurate + ready, no behavior change today.",
